---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PricingTiers from "../components/PricingTiers.astro";
---
<Layout title="Pricing · flipagent">
	<section class="hero" style="padding:64px 0 32px;">
		<div class="cmw cmw-bordered">
			<h1>Start free. Pay <span class="accent">when you scale</span>.</h1>
			<p class="lead">Credits cover everything: marketplace search, AI evaluation, deal discovery. Free is a one-time 500-credit trial; paid plans refill monthly. One unit, predictable budget, transparent costs.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section" style="padding-top:24px;">
		<div class="cmw cmw-bordered">
			<PricingTiers />
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section" style="padding-top:32px;">
		<div class="cmw" style="max-width:760px;">
			<h2 style="font-size:28px; letter-spacing:-0.02em; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:14px;">API <span class="accent">credits</span></h2>
			<p style="color:var(--text-2); font-size:15.5px; line-height:1.65;">
				Credits are consumed on every API request, varying by endpoint and feature. Free starts you with 500 credits — they're a one-time grant, not a monthly stipend. Paid plans refill on the 1st of each month (UTC). Cached responses cost 0 credits. If you connect your eBay account, marketplace reads route through eBay's REST API and don't decrement your balance either.
			</p>
			<table class="api" style="margin-top:16px;">
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>Feature</th>
						<th>Endpoint</th>
						<th style="text-align:right;">Credits</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>Search</td>
						<td><code>/v1/search</code>, <code>/v1/buy/*</code>, <code>/v1/sell/*</code>, <code>/v1/commerce/*</code>, <code>/v1/post-order/*</code></td>
						<td style="text-align:right;">1 / call</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Evaluate</td>
						<td><code>/v1/evaluate</code></td>
						<td style="text-align:right;">50 / call</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Discover</td>
						<td><code>/v1/discover</code></td>
						<td style="text-align:right;">250 / call</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Browser op</td>
						<td><code>/v1/browser/*</code></td>
						<td style="text-align:right;">5 / call</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Cached response</td>
						<td>any endpoint, when served from cache</td>
						<td style="text-align:right;">0</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>REST passthrough</td>
						<td>marketplace reads when eBay is connected</td>
						<td style="text-align:right;">0</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>
			<p style="color:var(--text-2); font-size:15.5px; line-height:1.65; margin-top:16px;">
				Free routes (uncounted): <code>/v1/health</code>, <code>/v1/me/*</code>, <code>/v1/keys/*</code>, <code>/v1/takedown</code>, <code>/v1/billing/*</code>, <code>/v1/capabilities</code>.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section" style="padding-top:32px;">
		<div class="cmw" style="max-width:760px;">
			<h2 style="font-size:28px; letter-spacing:-0.02em; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:14px;">Connect eBay for <span class="accent">free search</span></h2>
			<p style="color:var(--text-2); font-size:15.5px; line-height:1.65;">
				When you bind your API key to a connected eBay account, marketplace reads route through eBay's REST API directly — faster, more reliable, and they don't decrement your credit balance. Evaluate and discover still cost credits because the heavy lifting happens on our side (LLM matching, hazard model, cluster fan-out).
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section" style="padding-top:32px;">
		<div class="cmw" style="max-width:760px;">
			<h2 style="font-size:28px; letter-spacing:-0.02em; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:14px;">Going over</h2>
			<p style="color:var(--text-2); font-size:15.5px; line-height:1.65;">
				Once you exhaust your credits you'll get a <code>429</code>. Paid plans reset 00:00 UTC on the 1st of next month; Free is one-time, so a maxed-out Free key can only proceed by upgrading. Burst rate limits (per-minute, per-hour) sit alongside the credit budget and protect against runaway scripts; normal automation never trips them. We surface the next-plan-up math in your dashboard at 80% utilization.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section" style="padding-top:32px; padding-bottom:96px;">
		<div class="cmw" style="max-width:760px;">
			<h2 style="font-size:28px; letter-spacing:-0.02em; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:14px;">Enterprise &amp; self-host</h2>
			<p style="color:var(--text-2); font-size:15.5px; line-height:1.65;">
				<strong style="color:var(--text-1);">Enterprise</strong> — custom credit volume, dedicated infra, SLA, white-label. <a href="mailto:hello@flipagent.dev">hello@flipagent.dev</a>.
			</p>
			<p style="color:var(--text-2); font-size:15.5px; line-height:1.65;">
				<strong style="color:var(--text-1);">Self-host</strong> — the API server is open source. Run it with your own scraper credentials and your own LLM key; pay nothing to flipagent. Source on <a href="https://github.com/jinhokim98/flipagent">GitHub</a>.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
